critique: This document revokes the designation of three international organizations as public international organizations entitled to enjoy certain privileges, exemptions, and immunities. These organizations are the United Nations Relief and Rehabilitation Administration, the Inter-American Coffee Board, and the Intergovernmental Committee on Refugees. The document does not seem to have a strong ideological tilt. It appears to be an administrative action related to the cessation of these organizations. It doesn't directly address immigration, executive power, federalism, national security, economic regulation, or social inclusion. Therefore, most scores will be neutral.
